feat(display-tablets): add tablet display configuration feature

Add comprehensive tablet display configuration system allowing customization of:
- Display parameters (slide duration, cache, refresh intervals)
- Screen selection, ordering, and per-screen settings
- Type-specific settings for 6 screen types (summary, datetime, appointments, tasks, week/month calendars)

Technical implementation:
- Database: migration 017 adds `config` JSONB column to `display_tablets` table
- Domain: TabletDisplayConfig entity with TypeScript interfaces for all screen types and settings
- Validation: Zod schemas with comprehensive validation rules (durations, screen ordering, type-specific settings)
- Repository: updateDisplayTabletConfig method with JSON serialization
- API: GET and PUT endpoints for config management

New API endpoints:
- GET /v1/households/:householdId/display-tablets/:tabletId/config - Retrieve configuration
- PUT /v1/households/:householdId/display-tablets/:tabletId/config - Update configuration with validation

Configuration features:
- Validates slide duration (1-60s), cache (1-60min), refresh intervals (1-60min)
- Enforces unique consecutive screen ordering (0, 1, 2...)
- Validates screen-specific settings per type (colors, fonts, display modes, etc.)
- Auto-adds lastUpdated timestamp on each save
- Returns null for unconfigured tablets (mobile app uses built-in defaults)
- Access control: all members read, only caregivers modify

Backward compatibility: existing tablets continue working with null config.
